				\begin{document}$$\bar 3$$\end{document}m, Pnma, R3c, and R3m. b The relaxed 3D-cubic structure from the initial ones in a. c The organic molecule N(CH3)4+ located at A site. d The relaxed 1D (P63/m) structure which represents the experimental structure at the ambient pressure. e The relaxed 2D structure and f the relaxed 3D-hex (P63/mmc) structure.

Four 3D structures in Fig. 1a are derived by replacing the A-site cation of inorganic ABX3 perovskite by the non-polar N(CH3)4+ group and B-site cation by Sn2+. It is well known that the perovskite ABX3 compounds can have different lattice symmetries at different temperatures, e.g., the cubic structure with the Pm3¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
