Although the 3D-cubic perovskite structure is not the most energetically preferred at 0 GPa, it was suggested that the 3D-cubic perovskite can be synthesized and the electronic structure can be modified under a high pressure17. So, we apply a hydrostatic pressure up to 10 GPa on the 1D, 2D, 3D-cubic, and 3D-hex structures, respectively, to investigate the behavior of the structure under different pressures. We compare Htot\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
