Since the molecule N(CH3)4+ is at A site, we also considered the van der Waals (vdW) interactions for the structural relaxation. When the vdW interaction is included in the relaxation, the lattice constant is about 6.73 Å, which is smaller than ~7.04 Å (without vdW). However, for the pressure-dependent total enthalpy (Htot\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
